<span class="displaytext">the (candidate full) presidential committee today announced that former congresswoman nancy johnson has endorsed mayor (candidate last) for president. johnson represented connecticut in the united states house of representatives from 1983 until 2007. <p>"mayor (candidate last) will be a strong leader for our country," said johnson. "he has the experience and vision to be president, and his commitments to fiscal responsibility, keeping our country safe and providing families with more healthcare options will serve america well. rudy is the only candidate with the message needed to beat the (PARTY NAME) next fall." </p><p>"nancy is a distinguished public servant and was very effective representing the people of connecticut," said mayor (candidate last). "we're glad to have her support. she will be an asset for us in the state." </p><p>mayor (candidate last) appeared with congresswoman johnson at a press conference in hartford today. </p><p><strong><u>about congresswoman nancy johnson:</u></strong> </p><p>johnson was first elected to the united states house of representatives in 1982. she served on the house ways and means committee, where she chaired the subcommittee on health. she served in the connecticut senate from 1977 to 1983. </p><p>johnson currently serves as a resident fellow at harvard university's institute of politics. prior to her public service career, johnson was a teacher. she is a graduate of radcliffe college.</p></span>



